cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper discusses regularization techniques for deep neural networks, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks such as image classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Rademacher complexity, which is a measure of the complexity of a function class, indicating a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses image datasets, suggesting a possible fit with cs.CL (Computation and Language).
